ractices, alongside bioethics, to identify Jain perspectives on bioethical issues while highlighting the complexity of their personal, professional, and public dimensions. The book also features extensive original data-represented in visual graphs-based on an international survey the authors conducted with Jain medical professionals in India and diaspora communities of North America, Europe, and Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2022) 0aBioethicsxReligious aspectsxJainism. 0aMedicinexReligious aspectsxJainism. 7aRELIGION / Jainism.2bisacsh1 aBajželj, Ana, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishz978311075419308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520380578zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520380578zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520380578/original  a978-3-11-073915-2 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075419-3 EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-a